{"_id":"b0968020-1c52-11e9-85a5-7f61d3b02144","postId":"2009_06_using-socket-as-connected-socket-6c7c5ff1-54f8-3fe3-97aa-f9d00c023c6c","postUri":"https://blog.stephencleary.com/2009/06/using-socket-as-connected-socket.html","replyTo":"76184de0-1c4b-11e9-85a5-7f61d3b02144","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"23448e78d187fba56d8bc263081ac5d8","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com","message":"-1 is EOF - an End Of File notification. When you read a -1 from a socket, it means the other side of the socket has closed its connection.\r\n\r\nThere's nothing you can *do* about it other than respond in an appropriate way, whatever that means for your application. For many systems, the appropriate response is to wait a bit and reconnect.","date":"2019-01-20T01:28:29.273Z"}